headline: Nine months in, Starbucks CEO faces tall order in turnaround
summary: Nine months into his Starbucks tenure, investors are unsure if lightning will strike a third time.  Shares jumped more than 21% on August 13, the day Niccol was named CEO, on hopes he would inject the company with new vitality after several quarters of falling sales and pressure from activist investor Elliott Investment Management.  Starbucks shares closed up 0.3% on Wednesday.

headline: Analysis-Nine months in, Starbucks CEO faces tall order in turnaround
summary: (Reuters) -Starbucks CEO Brian Niccol earned a reputation on Wall Street as a miracle worker for wounded restaurant brands like Taco Bell and Chipotle.  Nine months into his Starbucks tenure, investors are unsure if lightning will strike a third time.  Shares jumped more than 21% on August 13, the day Niccol was named CEO, on hopes he would inject the company with new vitality after several quarters of falling sales and pressure from activist investor Elliott Investment Management.

headline: Billionaire Bill Ackman Continues to Sell Shares of Chipotle in Favor of an Industry-Leading Stock Where the Addressable Market Can 10X in 8 Years
summary: Pershing Square Capital Management's billionaire chief has sold most of his fund's stake in Chipotle over seven years, and is now piling into his new favorite stock.
